@startuml
title Linux boot chain and the physical-access adversary

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #f5f5f5
}

start
:BIOS / UEFI;
note right
  Critical first stage. UEFI is complex/proprietary.
  Out-of-band engines (Intel AMT, AMD PSP, IPMI, iLO)
  run beneath the OS. Alternatives: coreboot, Libreboot.
end note
:Bootloader (GRUB / LILO / Syslinux);
note right
  First binary of the distribution. Can edit kernel
  boot options -> evil maid attack. GRUB can unlock
  encrypted partitions; protect boot params + integrity.
end note
:initramfs (/boot, cpio, tmpfs);
note right
  Loads drivers/modules so init can run.
  Unlocks the encrypted root (LUKS, TPM-sealed key).
end note
:Kernel (/boot/vmlinuz);
note right
  Launched with parameters passed by the bootloader.
end note
:init (/sbin/init -> systemd);
:Runlevel / services\n(System V, systemd, OpenRC);
note right
  Starts system services and processes.
  Chain of trust relies on proprietary tooling:
  SecureBoot, TPM, OPAL self-encrypting drives.
  Mitigation also means disabling unused OOB services.
end note
stop
@enduml
